Naming
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Tiraskaraṇī (तिरस्करणी) — the Mahabharata cloak of invisibility worn by
warriors and divine actors to enter hostile fields unseen. The name was chosen
to root the engine in a non-Western privacy tradition: invisibility as
disciplined, intentional, reversible — not opaque, not deceptive.

